Fifty for Conway! His impressive start to his Test career continues. Really good knock! Was shaky to begin with but now looks really solid. Gets there as he clips this nicely through mid-wicket for three.
On middle, it is played to mid off.
Loopy ball, on off, Conway looks to defend as the ball takes the outside edge and rolls to square leg for a couple.
Tossed up, on off, Conway works it to mid on.
Floated on off, Conway defends it off his front foot.
Tossed up, full and off, Conway looks to go big but does not connect well. It goes of the toe end towards the bowler.
Loopy ball, outside off, left alone.
Flatter on  off, Conway cuts it to point.
Fuller and on off, Williamson strokes it to covers.
Slightly shorter in length and outside off. Williamson leaves it alone.
Beaten! This lands on a length and around off, pitches and moves away. Williamson is beaten as he tries to block.
Beauty! The pitch seems to have quickened up a touch. This lands on off and then holds its line. Williamson is beaten as he tries to block again.
Relentless stuff from the last three balls by Bumrah. Good length and on off, Williamson keeps it out this time. He plays this one right under his eyes, nice and late.
Once again plays it nice and late and onto the ground. Good testing over by Bumrah.
Tossed up on off, blocked.
Tossed up on off stump, Conway keeps it out again.
Floats it up on off, Conway pushes it to covers.
Flatter and on off, it is pushed back to the bowler.
On middle, defended nicely.
Slightly shorter, this is pushed to covers. A maiden by Jadeja.
Outside off, Williamson lets it go to the keeper.
Back of a length again and on off, Williamson is solid in defense.
On off, Williamson plays it to mid off.
Good length again and this one shapes away. Left alone.
This is brilliant from Bumrah. Again, lands it on off and then gets it to move away. Williamson looks to block but is beaten yet again. Can't do a lot about that delivery.
Back of a length and on off, blocked.
Outside off, an easy leave.
Attacks the stumps and it is kept out by Conway.
Loose! This angles into off and then moves away late. Conway is rooted to his crease and he ends up pushing at it away from the body. Gets beaten.

OUT! TAKEN! The bowling change has worked wonders and Conway is a goner shortly after getting to his half ton. Ishant is pumped up. Not the best of deliveries but he won't care. This is full and on the pads, Conway looks to flick. He seems a little early in the shot. It goes off the leading edge towards mid on. Shami moves to his left, stretches and takes a good catch. Can India get another before Stumps? They will surely have their tails up. This wicket will surely boost their energies. This could be a testing period for the new batsman.
Howout: c Mohammed Shami b Ishant Sharma

Commentary: Excellent first ball! Made him play! Fuller and on off, it is pushed to mid off.
Really good! This is on middle, Taylor plays it to mid off.
Starts off with a length delivery just outside off. Williamson leaves it alone. Bumrah gets good carry tk the keeper.
Back of a length now and on off, Williamson guides it to point.
Well bowled! Good length again, this holds its line after pitching. The line though is just outside off, left alone.
Besuty! Goes wide of the crease and then angles it into the off pole. Williamson looks to block but the ball pitches and moves away. Beats the outside edge.
Now brings this one back into the batter. Attakcs the off pole again. Williamson is solid in defense. Bumrah has overstepped so first runs for today, courtesy a no ball.
Does not find the gap. Bumrah goes a touch fuller this time and lands it on off. Probably looking for some movement in the air but there is none. Williamson plays it to point.

Edged but well short. Soft hands from Williamson. Length and on off, holds its line again. Williamson plays it late and with very soft hands. It goes off the outside edge but lands well short of second slip. A good first over by Bumrah.

Starts off with a big booming inswinger. Looking to hit the pad of Taylor who does plant his front foot a little too across at times. This one though is down the leg side. Taylor misses the flick and it goes to the keeper.
And again! Almost an action replay of the last ball. Another big inswinger but down the leg side. Taylor again misses the flick and it goes to the keeper.

Straighter than the last two deliveries but not as straight as he would have liked. This starts on off and then comes back in. Taylor looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. Ishant needs to start from outside off.
A lot better! However, not a lot of movement on this one. Length and just outside off, comes back in a little. Taylor plays it to mid on.
Another one on middle, Taylor works it to square leg.
Gets this one to hold its line after landing it on off. Blocked. A maiden to begin with by Ishant.
Again, really good carry for Bumrah but the line is outside off, left alone.
Angles this one into the pads, it is worked with the angle to square leg.
This one is just outside off, Williamson covers his off pole and lets it go. Haven't seen Bumrah getting a lot of movement in this Test. He's gotten good carry but not a lot of movement.
Slightly shorter this time and around off, Williamson hangs back, plays it late and to point.
Gets this one to zip through but the line is down the leg side. Williamson misses the flick and it goes to the keeper.
Better! Bumrah needs to make the batter play a lot more like he did on the last ball of this over. On off, the length is also good. Williamson blocks it out. A maiden by Bumrah too now.
Good length and on off, Taylor lunges and pushes to mid off.

On the fuller side this time, Taylor strokes it back to the bowler. A very tentative push there by Taylor. That was pitched up and there was an opportunity to score but Taylor was probably worried about the ball coming back in and ends up pushing it gently back to the bowler.
Ishant bends his back on this one. Lands it on off and gets some extra bounce. It hits the splice of the bat as Taylor looks to defend.

Missing leg easily! Ishant though really liked it. He was pleading. This time bowls the inswinger but it is a little too straight. Taylor looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. It rolls on the leg side. Leg bye taken. Still a run to be scored of the bat today.
That is a really good take by Pant. A short one, a surprise short delivery. Williamson ducks under it. It keeps rising as it goes to the keeper. Pant leaps and takes it nicely.
Solid as ever! On middle, Williamson gets right behind the line of the delivery and blocks it.
Good length again and on off, Taylor plays it late and on the off side.
First run of the bat today! On off and on a length. Taylor drops it on the off side and takes one. Ross is also off the mark.
A sharp short one, Williamson ducks under it.
Pushed the batsman on the back foot on the last ball and now gets hit on the front foot but the line is outside off. Left alone.
And again! Not on the stumps, Williamson need not play at it. Quite a lot of harmless deliveries from Bumrah.
Back of a length and on off, blocked.
Outside off; not played at.
Another single! Runs hard to come by but that has been throughout this game. Good disciplined bowling by India so far. On middle, this is worked on the leg side for one.
Movement of the pitch! Length and outside off, this one jags back in sharply. Williamson fails to put bat on ball and is hit high on the thigh pad.
On off, kept out.
A quiet enquiry by Kohli! Down the leg side, Williamson looks to flick but misses.
Finally Williamson scored his first run today! On middle, this is worked towards mid-wicket for one.
On off, Williamson plays it nice and late toward point.
On off, Williamson plays it to covers.
Another one outside off, left alone. Bumrah just hasn't been at his best with his accuracy. Way too many balls outside off.
The line was right this time but the length is way too short. Williamson rocks back and blocks it.
Better! Length and on off, Williamson plays it onto the ground. He needs to be a lot consistent with such deliveries.
And again! Goes back to bowling one outside off, Williamson would leave those all day long.
Straightaway he gets extravagant movement! The line though is just outside off, it moves away further. Taylor pulls his bat out of the way.
That is a beauty! Why didn't India start with him. This lands on off and on a length. It moves away late. Taylor is beaten as he tries to block. Shami probably needs to go a little fuller here.

FOUR! He does go fuller but is driven beautifully to the fence. That should not discourage Shami though as such deliveries can produce the edge. This is fuller and it shapes away from around off. Taylor creams it through covers for a boundary.
Extra bounce! He's steaming in here. Lands it on off and then gets it tot take off. Taylor gets hit high on the bat as he tries to block. It rolls in the vacant cover region for one.
Really good stuff! Making the batter play again. On off, blocked.

Really good from Shami! He made the batters play almost every ball he bowled in this over and caused problems. Something Ishant and Bumrah weren't doing a lot. This one is the inswinger. It lands outside off and jags back in. Williamson gets an inside edge onto the pads as he tries to block.

Ishant hasn't got the radar right with the inswingers! He is getting prodigious movement but the line is on the pads. Taylor looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. Pant dives to his left and gets a hand to it. A leg bye taken.
Really good from Ishant this time. Gets it to jag back in after landing it just outside off. Williamson looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Makes the batter play again by landing it on middle, blocked nicely.
On off, blocked. Good stuff in the last 10 balls. They are attacking the stumps a lot more and all of a sudden the two batters seem to be in a spot of bother.
This one is left alone but it is not a bad ball. It is just outside off.
That one does lob to short leg, it does hit the pad but not the bat. Angled into the pads, Williamson looks to flick but it hits the thigh pad and short leg takes it.
The stumps at the non-striker end plays as an extra fielder there. Fuller and on middle, this is driven back nicely but it hits the stumps at the other end.
And again, hits the splice. On off, Taylor stands tall and plays it onto the ground.
Attacks the stumps again. Taylor keeps it out.

Really well played in the end. The way he lets it go just shows how closely he's watching the delivery. Length and on off, Taylor initially looks to play at it but this moves away. He pulls his bat away.
Testing stuff! Just outside off. Taylor covers his off pole and leaves it alone.
Ends the over with a harmless nut well outside off. Left alone.
Angled down the leg side. Williamson misses the flick.
On middle, this is worked to mid-wicket.
Slightly fuller, this one comes back in. Williamson looks to push at it, it goes off the inner half through square leg for one.

FOUR! Was that a chance? Not really! That was a superb effort. This is on the pads, Taylor looks to flick but it goes off the glove or the shoulder of the bat. Pant moves to his left and then dives, does not get to it. It goes down to the fine leg fence.
Beaten! That is loose from Taylor. Yes, this is there to drive, it is full and outside off but he goes after to away from his body with his feet rooted to the crease. Gets beaten.
Good length and around off, this is pushed towards cover.
Good take by Pant again! Just outside off, this one stays low. Bounces in front of Pant who grabs it well.
Just outside off again, left alone again.
A little too straight this time. Williamson looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads.
Amother leave as this is once again bowled outside off.
Back of a length and on off, Williamson keeps it out.
Williamson probably misses out there. It is really full and outside off, he is late on the drive and it goes to point.
Back of a length and on off, this is played to point.
Good length now on middle, this is played to mid on.
Just outside off, Taylor shoulders arms to it. Not a lot of carry on that one as it goes on the bounce to the keeper.
On middle, Taylor hangs back and plays it to mid on.
Well fielded! On middle, this is worked nicely but the man at mid-wicker dives to his left and stops it.
Another one on off, kept out.
Back of a length and on off, Williamson pushes it to covers.
Back of a length and on off, Williamson defends it.
Back of a length again, Williamson hangs back and keeps it out.
Another one on a length, blocked.
Outside off, left alone.
On middle, Williamson works it to mid-wicket.

OUT! Taken! That is a really good catch by Gill and India have gotten the wicket they so desperately wanted. The Drinks break does the job for the Indians and they are absolutely pumped up. A well-deserved wicket for Shami. He has been outstanding so far and he gets the reward. He lands it just behind a driving length. Taylor goes for the drive but due to the extra bounce Shami is getting it goes off the higher part and hence, uppishly to the right of Gill at extra cover. He dives and takes a sharp catch. Can India build on this? New Zealand still trail by 100.
Howout: c Shubman Gill b Mohammed Shami

Commentary: Nicholls is off the mark! Angled into the pads, Henry looks to work it on the leg side but closes the face of the bat early. It goes off the leading edge towards cover for one.
Close! This lands on off and then comes back in. Williamson looks to block but it goes off the inner half through square leg for one.

FOUR BYES! That comes in a long way. This lands well outside off and comes back in. Nicholls leaves it alone. It keeps swinging in and goes past the dive of Pant who had no chance and down to the fine leg fence.
Solid! Good length and on off, blocked.
Fuller in length again but the line is outside off, left alone.

All of a sudden there is a spring in the step of the Indians. That is a jaffa from Bumrah but how good did Williamson play that. This lands on off and then moves away late. Williamson is almost committed to a front foot defense but right at the end, he leaves it alone. Brilliant. He too is keeping an eye on the ball right till the end.
Outside off, left alone.
Loose! Perhaps a loss in concentration and since, runs scoring has been difficult, he just got tempted to go after that. It is short and outside off. Williamson throws his bat at it but is beaten.
Bumrah is starting to get into his element now. Good length and it holds its line from off. Williamson is beaten as he tries to play the original trajectory.
Excellent! Makes the batter play again by landing it on off. Blocked. Williamson again plays it very late with soft hands. Perfect technique to play in such conditions.
A bumper to end, ducked under.
BEATEN! Shami is bowling with a lot of fire here! This is a back of a length delicery, really gets it to bounce nicely. Nicholls hops and tries to block but it goes just past the glove.
FOUR! Put away! That cut shot has been nailed! Short and wide outside off, Nicholls hops and cuts it over point for a boundary.
Angled into middle, it is worked to mid-wicket.
On middle, Nicholls looks to block but it goes off the inside edge down to fine leg for one.
Outside off, left alone.
A harmless delivery to end. Outside off, left alone.
Bumrah starting to find his line and length. On off, on a length. Blocked.
On the pads, Nicholls tries to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. Bumrah is really getting the ball to zip through nicely.
Well wide outside off this time. Easy leave.
Really good from Bumrah. He's attacking the stumps and creating problems now. This lands just around leg and this straightens. Nicholls looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pad.
Angles one across from the off pole. Nicholls left it alone.
A good maiden over by Bumrah! On off, it is kept out nicely.
On middle, Williamson works it to mid-wicket.
Slips this one down the leg side. Williamson lets it be. Pant does not collect it cleanly but no runs conceded.
On off, this is pushed to covers.
Another one on the stumps, kept out.
Fuller and around off, Kane pushes it to mid off.
A good finish by Shami. Length and on off, shapes away. Williamson plays it late and with soft hands. Onto the ground.
Length delivery on off, Nicholls blocks it out.
Good length ball outside off, Nicholls decides to leave as he raises his blade. The ball gets off the bottom half and goes towards slips.
On a length on middle, Nicholls defends it watchfully. Bumrah has overstepped and will have to reload again.
Fuller on off, defended with ease.
Good length delivery outside off, Nicholls lets it sail through.
On middle, Nicholls clips it to deep square leg for a single.
FOUR! Low full toss on middle, Kane Williamson whips it towards deep mid-wicket for a boundary. He has been patient throughout and finally fetches himself a boundary. His first boundary of the day.
Just outside off, left alone.
Good length and on off, Nicholls guides it to point.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! India have another and the pressure they have been building has paid off. Nicholls walks back for a single digit score. He could have left that one. Yes, Ishant is bowling from around the wicket, it is angling into him but this was quite wide outside off. It lands in the 6th stump channel. Nicholls prods forward and reaches out for it. This one lands and holds its line. It goes off the outside edge between first and the second slip fielder. Rohit dives to his right and takes it. Can India get another one before Lunch?
Howout: c Rohit Sharma b Ishant Sharma

Commentary: Watling is off the mark! On off, it shapes back in. Watling works it down to fine leg for one.

Lovely stuff from Ishant. Something about this Indian attack after the loss of Taylor. They have been hitting the right lines and lengths and causing problems. On off, Williamson looks to defend the original trajectory but the ball moves away and whizzes past the outside edge.
On off, this time he blocks it solidly.
Big swing! Shorter and on off, shapes away. Watling lets it be.

OUT! TIMBER! India on fire here! They have another one and half the side back in the hut for the Kiwis and they still trail by another 82 runs. This is a beauty! Too good. This lands on middle, Watling does nothing wrong as he tries to defend the original trajectory. The ball pitches and then moves away. Hits the top of middle and off. Shami is ecstatic, the fans are ecstatic. Game on. Watling could have put in a better stride forward. He was rooted to his crease there and hence, could not adjust to the movement. Also, brilliant from Kohli, he's chopping and changing the ends of his bowlers exceptionally. The last 3 out of the 4 wickets have all come in the first over of a new spell of a bowler.
Howout: b Mohammed Shami

Commentary: Good length again and on middle, kept out.
Another one on off, blocked.
On middle, this is worked to mid-wicket.
Down the leg side. Colin looks to flick but misses.
Fuller length, bowls it straighter, Williamson defends it off the front foot.
Length delivery on the fifth stump channel, Williamson shoulders arms.
Fullish length on middle, angling in, Williamson tickles it to short mi-wicket.
Length delivery on middle, big inward movement, Williamson shuffles across a bit as he looks to hit it on the leg side. He gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Good length delivery on off, nipping away, Williamson looks to defend. The ball finds the outside edge but Williamson played it with soft hands, thus, gets carried towards first slip on one bounce.
An inswinger on middle, Williamson blocks it out. All smiles in the Indian camp right now. THAT WILL BE LUNCH ON DAY 5.
FOUR! What a way to start post Lunch! Serves a half-volley on off, Colin de Grandhomme leans into the shot and drives it through the covers for a boundary. Lovely cover drive from the mullet man.
Fuller on middle, de Grandhomme pushes it back to the bowler.

Length delivery on off, Colin de Grandhomme looks to work it over mid-wicket but gets an inside edge onto the pads. He is pretty clear with his intent. He is going to play his natural game, that is to attack.
Fuller on off, blocked out.
On a length outside off, left alone.
Good length delivery on off, angling in, de Grandhomme lets it sail through.
Flatter and quicker on leg, pushed back to the bowler.
Tossed up on leg, worked on the leg side for a single.
Fuller on middle, blocked out.
Floated it up on off, pushed back to the bowler.
Loopy ball on middle, guided through mid-wicket for a single. Jadeja has overstepped. No ball signaled.
Full and tossed up on leg, flicked through square leg for a run.
On middle and leg, tucked towards square leg for another single.
Length delivery on off, Colin de Grandhomme pulls it towards mid-wicket. Ashwin runs to grab it but it's far away from him. Two taken.
Length ball on off, nudged towards mid-wicket for one.
Good length ball on middle, blocked out.
Outside off, swinging in, Williamson shoulders arms.
Length ball on off, Williamson is solid in his defense.
Fuller on off, nudged on the leg side.
Flatter delivery on leg, worked on the leg side.
On off, tapped towards point.
Slower through the air, pushed back to the bowler.
Quicker one on leg, defended out.
Tossed up on off, pushed back to the bowler.
Fuller on middle, CdG blocks it out. A maiden for Jadeja.
Fuller length on off, Williamson taps it towards point.
Length delivery on off, Williamson keeps it out.
Good length ball on middle, angling in, Williamson pushes it back to the bowler off the back foot.
Length delivery on off, Williamson defends it onto the pitch.
On a length on off, Williamson is late into his defense. The ball goes off the outside edge behind gully for a couple of runs. 150 up for the Kiwis.
Length delivery on off, blocked out.
Fuller on middle, Colin de Grandhomme works it off the inner half of his blade towards mid off. He gets a single. 150 up for New Zealand.
Fuller on middle, Williamson prods and defends it watchfully.
Tossed up on off, Williamson misses his cut shot. A little bit of excitement from the Indian players but no edge though.
Flatter on middle, Williamson defends it on the on side.
Quicker on off, Williamson cuts it towards backward point. Gill does well to put in a dive and stop the ball. He keeps it to a single.
Drifting on leg, Colin de Grandhomme clips it to mid-wicket.
Bumrah goes wide of the crease, he angles it into the middle pole, hoping for it to holds its line. It goes straight on and it is played to mid on.
Nice and late! Williamson lets the ball come to him and guides it right at the end towards point.
Once again, Bumrah bowls a length ball on off, Williamson lets the ball do its bit and plays it onto the ground right next to his body.
On off, kept out.
Angled into the pads, Williamson works it to mid-wicket.
A maiden by Bumrah. Good one too as he made Williamson play almost every ball. On middle, kept out.
Fuller on middle, pushed back to the bowler. He is not able to find turn at the moment.
Shorter on leg, Colin de Grandhomme looks to clip it away but misses. He gets hit on the thigh pad. The ball rolls behind square and he grabs a single. Might have got an inside edge there.
Tossed up on off, steered towards point.
Loopy delivery outside off, Williamson rocks back and punches it towards point.
Fuller on off, blocked out.
Drifted it on leg, tucked towards square leg. That might be Jadeja's last spell for the session as the new ball is available.
Good length delivery outside off, nipping away, Colin de Grandhomme is beaten on the outside edge. Swing straightaway from Mohammed Shami as he bowls it with the new duke ball.
Short of a length, Colin de Grandhomme steers it towards gully. Rahane couldn't make a clean stop and allows a single.
FOUR LEG BYES! Back of a length delivery on leg, Kane Williamson misses his flick. The ball runs off the pads towards fine leg for a boundary.
Short of a length delivery on off, a bit swing movement, Williamson shoulders arms.
FOUR! Short and wide outside off, Kane Williamson works it past point for a boundary. India needs to be careful here. They should not allow leaking runs like that with the new ball.
Good length delivery outside off, left alone.
EXCELLENT FROM JADEJA! Short and on middle, this is pulled hard through square leg. Jadeja runs to his right quickly, stops it, gets back to his feet in no time and keeps it to one.
Back of a length and on off, Williamson pushes it to covers.
Gets this one to shape inwards but the line is down the leg side. Williamson looks to flick but misses.
Back of a length and on off, Williamson pushes it to covers. Not seen the new ball do a lot so far. Just the two in 10, one from Shami and the other from Ishant.
Good leave! Length and outside off, it does come in a little but not enough to make the batter play.
Another one outside off, Ishant is trying to get it back in from that line which he is not able to frkm today morning. Left alone again.

OUT! LBW! Shami is on song here today! Yet another wicket for him. Third so far and the second new ball does the work for India. Shami uses the crease extremely well here. Goes wide, lands it on off and then gets it to jag back in. Colin decides to play back but he does so outside the line. It goes past the inside edge and hits the pad. The finger is raised as soon as the Indians start appealing. India are into the bowling all-rounders. Still 55 away.
Howout: lbw b Mohammed Shami

Commentary: That is a confident shot to begin with! Length and on off, this is driven on the up but to covers. Risky to drive on the up on this surface but he did it well here.
Well bowled and well left. This time he bowls it from close to the stumps, this starts on off and then shapes away. Jamieson leaves it nicely.
And again, bowls it from closer to the stumps, it is the outswinger again but outside off, Kyle lets it be.
Another good confident shot by Jamieson but this time he gets runs for it. Three of them. Length again, he strokes it on the up through mid off, Ashwin gives to a chase and saves a run for his side.
A short one to end on middle, it is tucked to mid-wicket. End of a successful over for Shami.
Plays it on the up again! On middle, it is behind a driving length. This is worked through mid-wicket for a couple. Good start by the tall pacer.
And again! Length and on off, Jamieson strokes it through covers for two. He is hitting it well so far but all these on the up shots are difficult.
That is a wild swing! Not sure where that came from. Outside off and on a length. Jamieson looks to go downtown but is beaten.

Finds the gap again! So the intentions are clear here, Kyle wants to score quickly and it may not be a bad idea. Length and outside off, he looks to power it through covers but it goes off the splice but in the gap for two.
Away from the fielder yet again. On middle, Jamieson once again looks to hit it on the up. He mistimes it but wide of mid off for two.
Ishant attacks the stumps this time and Jamieson looks to go over mid-wicket. He plays a hack but it goes off the inner half through that region for two. Productive over for the Kiwis.
Two more! On middle, this is worked through square leg for two.
Two more! Quite a lot of twos in the last few overs and runs coming a little quickly now! On middle, it is clipped through square leg for two more. Trail below 40 now.
Another one on a length, Williamson plays it late and onto the ground.
Play and a miss! Outside off, Williamson does go after it initially but in the end pulls his bat back.

NOT OUT! Impact umpire's call and wickets hitting also umpire's call! Good review. It could have gone either way. Top delivery too. Length and on off, this one lands and then straightens. Williamson is squared up as he tries to block. It goes past the outside edge and hits the back pad. A huge appeal but turned down. Shami wants it to be reviewed and Kohli does so. Replays roll in and it initially shows a spike on Ultra Edge when the ball passes the bat but the third umpire says no bat involved. Hawk Eye shows the on-field call remains.
Good length and on off, kept out.
Beaten! Length and around off, this one zips through. Kyle is beaten as he pushes at it. It won't be easy hitting Bumrah on the up.
This time he does though as he strokes it through covers for one.
On middle, Williamson works it to mid-wicket.
Just outside off, once again, Williamson thinks of playing at it but righ at the end leaves it alone.
On middle, defended nicely.
Good stop in the end. Outside off, Kane lets it be. The ball wobbles away from Pant. He sticks both his hands to his right and stops it.
Length delivery on off, Jamieson pushes it towards point for a single.
FOUR! Shami drops it short on middle, Kane Williamson picks the length early, pulls it towards deep mid-wicket for a boundary. Brings down the deficit to 32.
Length delivery on off, worked towards mid on and rotates the strike.
Short ball on middle, Kyle Jamieson looks to pull but misses. A lot of effort for Shami to bowl a bouncer to Kyle Jamieson.
SIX! That is long! Good length ball on leg, Kyle Jamieson lofts it over long on for a maximum. The crowd is enjoying that. He is looking to up the ante.

OUT! CAUGHT! Mohammed Shami puts a full stop to Jamieson's counter-attack. Jamieson was looking to reduce the deficit as quickly as possible. He did succeed somewhat but Shami gets the wicket which was starting to worry India. Shami bowls a back of a length delivery on middle, Kyle Jamieson didn't connect it that well. The ball goes off the top edge as he swings his blade, was in the air for quite some time before Jasprit Bumrah grabs it with both hands at deep square leg. Very well taken by Bumrah as that was very near to the ropes. Kyle Jamieson was a man on a mission but so is Mohammed Shami for India. He picks up his fourth.
Howout: c Jasprit Bumrah b Mohammed Shami

Commentary: The inside edge saves Southee! Length and on off, this one jags back in. Southee looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Slightly fuller and on middle, this is pushed to mid off.
Again the inside edge saves Southee. He probably felt a short one is coming but it is full and on middle, Southee looks to flick but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
On middle, kept out.
JUST SHORT! This is full and outside off Souther looks to jam it out but it goes off the outside edge, lands short of second slip.
Two to end the over. Southee is off the mark. A full toss on the pads, Tim works it through square leg for two. He was looking for a yorker but ends up bowling a full toss.
FOUR! Shami loses his line here. Bowls it down the leg side, Kane Williamson clips it fine enough to get past through Pant to the fine leg fence.
Down the leg side again, Williamson misses his flick this time. The ball goes off the hips towards short fine leg. The batters sneak a leg bye.
Fuller on off, Southee defends it watchfully.
Fuller length on off, Southee pushes it back to the bowler.
Good length delivery on off, Southee works this one off the outside edge towards backward point. He picks up a single. 200 up for New Zealand.
Fullish delivery on middle, Williamson guides it towards long on. Jadeja gives it a chase and keeps it to two.
Well played in the end by Southee! Back of a length and on off, it gets big on the batter. Southee does well to take one hand off the handle. It goes on the bounce to gully.
On middle, this is pushed to mid on.
Not off the middle but two! On middle, it is a length ball. Southee lifts it over the bowler's head. The ball stops at it nears the ropes. Two taken.
A single now! On the pads, this is worked through square leg for one.
Back of a length and on off, this is pushed to covers.
Outside off, left alone.
FOUR LEG BYES! Bonus runs for New Zealand. The trail under 10 now. A short one on the body. Southee got into a tangle. He looks to sway away but it hits the body and goes down to the fine leg fence.
Back of a length and on off, kept out.
On off, not the kind of zip on this one as we saw on the deliveries today morning. It is guided to point.
Another bumper, Southee ducks under. Shami seems tired, this will probably be his last over of this spell.
Outside off, some gentle movement away. Southee slashes but misses.
SAFE! More fortunate runs for Southee! On the pads, he tries to flick but closes the face of the bat early. It goes off the leading edge over point for two.
Short of a length outside off, Williamson slices it towards deep point as he plays a square cut. He gets a single.

DROPPED! Tough chance but will count as a drop! Fuller length on off, Tim Southee looks to loft it but gets the toe end of the bat back to the bowler. Ishant Sharma didn't manage to hold onto that one as he puts his right hand out to catch it. The ball hits the palm and rolls on the leg side. A single taken.
Short ball on middle, Southee sits under it.
An inswinger on middle and leg, Southee looks to defend but gets beaten. The ball hits the thigh pad and rolls on the off side. The batters sneak a run of leg bye.
Fullish length on off, Kane Williamson saw the width and plays a confident cover drive. But straight to the cover fiedler.
Quicker and full on middle, blocked out by Williamson.
Down the leg side, Southee gets hit on the pads. He hands over the strike to Williamson of leg bye.
Length delivery on off, Williamson dabs it towards third man for a single.
Short of a length on off, Southee hops onto the crease and taps it on the off side. He takes off for a quick single.
Fuller length on off, a bit late away swing movement, Williamson drives it towards mid off.
Outside off, left alone.

FOUR! Back of a length on off, Kane Williamson guides it past point for a boundary. That boundary means New Zealand is into the lead. Looks like Shami is tiring out but Kohli is persisting with him to continue his spell. Williamson moves onto 49.
Short of a length on middle, Southee ducks underneath.
Good length ball on middle, Southee does well to hand over the strike to his skipper.
Fuller length, angling in, Williamson defends it watchfully.
Fuller again on off, pushed back to the bowler.
Goes full again on middle, guided towards point.

OUT! CAUGHT! Very rarely you see Kane Williamson play away from his body. His long vigilance at the crease ends. Sharma bowls a short of a length ball on the fifth stump channel, nipping away, Kane Williamson is tempted to play a cut and has a go at it. The ball finds the outside edge and goes to Virat Kohli who is standing at almost a third slip position. He won't drop those. Good captaincy by Virat Kohli to keep himself at third slip. Williamson falls one short of a half ton. The scorecard might just show 49 but what an innings that was. He battled through really tough conditions. He just being out there was extrmely important. Had he been dismissed earlier, the Kiwis could have well been bowled out till now. Also, timely wicket for the Indians. The lead is a slender one and they would now hope they can take the remaining two quickly.
Howout: c Virat Kohli b Ishant Sharma

Commentary: On middle, blocked.
FOUR! Poor ball from Ashwin and Tim capitalises! This is short and outside off, it is slapped through covers for a boundary.
On the pads, it is worked to mid-wicket.
A single as this is guided towards point.
This is quicker and it comes in from outside off. Blocked.
Kust outside off to end. Left alone.
SIX! Southee can bat too! Short of a length on middle, Southee shuffles across and heaves it over long on for a maximum. India can't let this tail wag.
Slower delivery on off, Southee defends it well.
Serves it down the leg side, Southee leaves it alone.
Down the leg side again, a bit slow this time, Southee watches the ball pass by.
Bowls a low full toss on middle, Southee whips it to deep square leg for a couple. Useful runs for New Zealand. They lead by 17.
Short of a length on off, Southee punches it off the back foot towards covers. Ravichandran Ashwin does well to put in a dive and stop that.
Tossed up on off, blocked.
Another one tossed up on off, kept out.

OUT! RAHANE HANGS ON! Ashwin gets rid of another left-hander. Good captaincy by Kohli to bring him on. This is tossed up on middle, a lot slower. It lands and spins away. Takes the outside edge as Wagner looks to defend. Goes quickly to Rahane at first slip who takes it on the second attempt.
Howout: c Ajinkya Rahane b Ravichandran Ashwin

Commentary: No ball! Boult has overstepped! On middle, kept out.
A single as this is pushed down to long on.

NOT OUT! That is nowhere near the bat and the ball is also going down leg. This lands around leg and then spins in. Southee looks to sweep but it lobs of something to leg slip. India appeal and the finger is raised. Southee reviews straightaway. Ultra Edge shows a spike when it is near the pads and Hawk Eye shows it to be going down leg. Southee survives to fight another day.
Very full and on off, it is hit to mid off.
BEATEN! Back of a length on leg, Boult looks to work it over the keeper's head but misses.
Shortish again on leg, Boult defends.
FOUR! What a shot! Bowls it fuller on middle, Boult moves across and lofts it straight over the bowler's head for a boundary. Crucial runs for New Zealand.
Length delivery on off, Boult swings his bat but connects it with thin air around him.
On a length on off, Boult taps it towards covers.
Length delivery on middle, clipped to backward square leg for a couple.
Floated it up on off, blocked out.
Fuller on leg, worked towards mid on.
Tossed up on middle, Southee is solid in his defense.
Bowls it full again on leg, worked on the leg side.
Loopy delivery on off, defended on the off side.
Slower and fuller on middle, knocked to long on for a run.
SIX! Welcomes Jadeja with a biggie! Short ball on middle, Tim Southee stays back in the crease, has all the time in the world, and muscles it over deep mid-wicket for a maximum.

OUT! BOWLED! Two deliveries is what it takes for Jadeja to sum up the innings! Fires a quicker ball on leg, Tim Southee looks to guide it towards third man. He was late into his shot and gets an inside edge onto the pads. Unlucky for Southee the ball rolls back onto the stumps. New Zealand end with 249 with a lead of 32 runs. THAT WILL BE TEA ON DAY 5.
Howout: b Ravindra Jadeja

Commentary: Starts off with a length ball, it shapes away a little. Left alone.
Three! India are underway and so is Rohit! Fuller and on off, this one shapes away. Sharma looks to drive but it goes off the outer half through backward point for three.
Another lovely outswinger. It starts on middle and then moves away. Gill looks to defend but it goes off the outer half to point.
Another outswinger but this line is well outside off, left alone.
One more ball outside off, Gill does not play at it again.

Almost! Superb stuff from Southee! He got the last few deliveries to go away and gets this one back in from outside off. Gill leaves it and it goes really close past the off pole. A good first over by Southee.
Starts with a length ball on off, angling away, Sharma defends it to point.
Length ball on the pads, Sharma tucks it towards square leg for a single.
Short of a length on middle, nudged towards mid-wicket.
Outside off, angling away, left alone by Gill.
Fullish delivery outside off, Gill leaves it untouched.
Another full delivery outside off, Gill shoulders arms.
Snorter! Good length delivery on off, Sharma looks to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Short of a length on middle, Sharma blocks it to mid on.
Good length delivery on middle, nipping away, Sharma misses his attempted defense. The ball kisses the outside edge and goes to the slip cordon.
Full length delivery on middle, Sharma defends it back to the bowler.
Length delivery outside off, Sharma lets it sail through.
On a length on middle, Sharma is solid in his defense.
Bowls a half-volley on leg, Gill tucks it to backward square leg for a couple.
Length delivery on middle and leg, coming back in, Gill hits it off the inside edge onto the pads. Half-hearted appeal for an LBW from Boult. Nothing from the umpire.
Angling too far, outside off, Gill allows it to go through.
Very full on off, Gill keeps it out.
On off, angling in, Gill opens the face of the bat, pushes it towards covers.
Full around middle and leg, clipped towards mid-wicket.
Good length delivery, outside off, swinging away, Sharma watches the ball pass by.
Fuller on off, nipping away, Sharma leans into the shot. The ball goes off the outside edge towards backward point.
Full again on off, Sharma guides it past backward point this time for a run.
Length delivery around off, swinging away, Gill lets it for the keeper to collect.
Length delivery on middle, Gill whips it to square leg.
On middle, Gill blocks it out.
Short of a length on leg, Sharma is late into his pull. The ball gets off the top edge on the leg side. Watling makes a run but falls too short.
Outside off, nipping away, Sharma looks to defend but misses. The ball zips past the outside edge, into the keeper's mitts.
Length delivery around middle, clipped towards square leg.
Good length ball on off, Sharma defends it well.
Length delivery on off, Sharma blocks this one.
FOUR! First boundary for India and for Rohit Sharma as well! Short of a length on off, Rohit Sharma cuts it past point for a boundary.
A length ball around off, nipping in, Gill looks to defend but misses. He gets hit on the thigh pad. An appeal for an LBW but turned down.
Around middle, worked on the leg side.
Back of a length delivery on off, Gill ignores that.
Fuller and outside off, Gill makes a leave.
Fuller length on middle, a proper inswinger, Gill clears his front leg and guides it towards short mid-wicket.
Length delivery outside off, angling away, Gill leaves it alone.
Length ball outside off, Sharma does not offer any strokeplay.
Fuller on off, Sharma drives it towards mid off.
PLAY AND A MISS! Good length delivery outside off, Sharma is tempted to play over the infield. He connects it with thin air and gets beaten.
FOUR! Connects it this time! An inswinger on leg, Rohit Sharma flicks it towards the fine leg region. Kyle Jamieson puts in a dive but couldn't get a hand at it.
Way outside off, left alone.
Length delivery outside off, angling away, Sharma shoulders arms.
Goes wide of the crease and angles it into the middle pole, this is worked through square leg for two.
Nicely played! Fuller and around off, Gill leans into it, lets the ball swing and plays it nicely to mid off.
Again! On middle, Gill plays it right under his eyes on the off side.
This one is bowled outside off, left alone.
Just a push for two! Fuller and on middle, Gill strokes it off the middle, it bounces and goes over the bowler for two.
A couple more! On middle, this is worked through square leg and two is taken.
Angled into the pads, he was probably looking to shape the ball away but this is flicked through square leg for two. Jamieson has also overstepped.
Back of a length and on off, blocked.
Back of a length again and on off, Sharma stands tall and plays it late on the off side.
Kyle has started a little too short. Once again it is a back of a length ball outside off. Left alone.
Very full this time and outside off. Sharma looks to drive, hits the ground in the process and it goes to the keeper.
Really wide outside off, left alone. Kyle hasn't started all that well so far.
Outside off, Sharma leaves it alone again. Not a good first over by Kyle.
Slightly fuller and outside off, Gill leaves it alone.
That was firmly hit but for no runs! On middle, this is flicked but to the man at mid-wicket. That was right off the middle. Lovely shot.
On middle, this is kept out nicely.

OUT! THAT IS PLUMB! New Zealand get an early wicket. India still behind by 8. He played across the line there. Southee goes full and gets the ball to come back in from off. Shubman Gill looks to flick but misses, he gets hit on the pads. An appeal and the finger is raised. Gill has a word with his partner but he does not review and rightly so. Can they get another before the deficit is wiped off?
Howout: lbw b Tim Southee

Commentary: Pujara is off the mark! On the pads, this is worked down to fine leg for one.
More runs! Fuller and around off, this shapes away. Sharma looks to defend but it goes off the outer half through backward point for two.
Good length delivery outside off, seaming away, Pujara doing what he does best. Shoulders arms and lets it sail through. Much better line and length from Jamieson.
Length delivery outside off, Pujara leaves it untouched.
Length delivery outside off, Pujara lets it sail through.
Fuller on off, an outswinger, Pujara blocks it out.
On a length outside off, Pujara does not offer any strokeplay. Watling behind the stumps is heard shouting "GOOD LENGTH" lad.
An inswinger on middle, Pujara defends it watchfully.
Outside off, nipping away, Sharma shoulders arms.
Good length delivery on middle, swinging away, Sharma taps it towards gully.
Slightly shorter on middle, clipped towards mid-wicket for a run.
Short ball on middle, Pujara sits under this one.
Short of a length on middle, angling in, Pujara blocks it out.
Fuller on middle, a straighter one, Pujara works it on the leg side. India trail by 4 runs.
Fuller on middle, Sharma blocks it on the leg side.
Short ball on middle, Sharma hooks it towards deep square leg for a single. Loud shout for a 'CATCH' but well short of the fielder.
Fuller on middle, coming back in, Pujara tucks it to the left of the short leg fielder.
Fuller on off, blocked out.
Bowls a short one on middle, Pujara ducks under it.
Into the gap and will get three! Fuller on middle and leg, Pujara flicks it through mid-wicket and collects three runs. India wipes out the deficit. The scores are level.
Full and on off, Pujara is solid in his defense.
Good length ball, outside off, seaming away, Pujara shoulders arms.
Fuller length on middle, Pujara pushes it on the on side.
Length delivery on off, Pujara gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Bowls a straighter one on off, Pujara defends it onto the pitch.
Length delivery on off, nipping in, well left by Pujara.
On a length outside off, Sharma is happy to leave that.
Fuller on off, angling away, Sharma defends it watchfully.
Short on off, Rohit Sharma gets into the position and pulls it towards deep square leg. He gets a single.
Fuller length on middle, a little bit of late movement, Pujara works it on the leg side.
Length delivery on middle, Pujara keeps his eyes on the ball and blocks it out.
Around off, Pujara defends it watchfully.
BEATEN! Peach of delivery on off, shaping away, Sharma prods and looks to defend. The ball zips past the outside edge, into Watling's gloves.
Bowls it full this time, on middle, Sharma clips it on the leg side.
That's the line and length Jamieson will target! Bowls a length delivery on off, Sharma leaves it alone. Jamieson will look to make the batters play with that line outside off.
Good length delivery outside off, dabbed towards gully.
Length delivery on off, Sharma gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Length ball on off, Sharma works it with soft hands towards backward point. He collects a couple of runs.
Change of angle for Boult. He comes over the wicket, bowls back of a length delivery on middle, Pujara blocks it out.
Around off, Pujara deals with it well.
Short ball on middle, Pujara sits under it.
Another short ball on middle, Pujara ducks again.
Fuller length outside off, shaping in, Pujara defends it on the off side.
Comes round the wicket, bowls a length ball outside off, Pujara leaves it alone.
On off, this is guided to point.
Length again and on middle, kept out.
On middle, defended.
Outside off, left alone.
On middle, this is worked to mid-wicket.
A short one to end, it is outside off, left alone.
Outsidr off, left alone.
On middle, kept out.
FOUR! Delightful! Lovely. Full and on middle, this is driven nicely past the mid on fielder and this races away to the fence.
Outside off, left alone.
Another one which is not on the stumps, not played at.
A short one, a quick short ball. It is ducked under.
Fuller and on middle, this is played back to the bowler.
Another one on a length, left alone.
Sharma leaves another ball as this too is well outside off.
On middle, this is worked to mid-wicket.
Good running! On off, this is dropped towards cover for one.
Outside off again, Pujara this time lets it go.
A short one, this does not bounce a lot. Sharma looks to pull but misses.
On the pads, Sharma looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads.
On off, Sharma looks to block it but it goes off the inner half through square leg for one.
On the stumps, this is kept out nicely.
Well bowled, angles this away from the off pole. Rohit looks to defend but is beaten.
Outside off, Pujara points his bat skywards and lets it be.
Outsidr off, this is guided to point.
Risky shot! Length and on off, this is pushed to covers. He played that away from the body.
One more awayswinger. It is outside off so left alone.
Just outside off, Sharma watches it go to the keeper.
A single eventually! On middle, this is worked towards mid on. Rohit wants a run but Pujara waits, he sees it beats the dive and then takes it.
On middle, defended.
Lovely stop! Fuller and on off, this is driven towards mid off. Williamson slides to his left and stops it.
This time he finds the gap! Pushes this shortish delivery through covers for two.
Almost! Rohit looks to play a ball which is slightly fuller in length off the back foot. He gets an inside edge but it goes beside the stumps.
A short one and on middle, this is pulled through square leg for one.
On middle, kept out.
Outside off, left alone.
Beautifully bowled! Late movement there! Bowls a length delivery on the fifth stump channel, Sharma went for the drive but gets beaten.
Fuller on off, Sharma defends it off the front foot.
Full again on middle, Sharma flicks it through mid-wicket and picks up two comfortably.
Fuller outside off, Sharma watches the ball pass by.
Length delivery on off, nipping back in, Sharma gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Fullish delivery on the middle pole, pushed back to the bowler.
Length delivery outside off, Pujara taps it towards point.
Fuller but outside off, Pujara leaves it for the keeper to collect.
Good length delivery on middle, swinging in, Pujara blocks it out.

FOUR! Pitches it down the leg, Pujara takes all the time in the world before flicking it towards fine leg. Jamieson came running across and did all the hard work to stop the boundary, but couldn't do so. A boundary for Pujara. India lead by 19.
Good length outside off, left alone.
Fuller and outside off, Pujara leaves it untouched.
Length delivery outside off, Sharma decides not to play.
Fuller length outside off, Sharma drives it towards CdG at short cover.
Back of a length delivery on off, Sharma defends it on the off side.
Fuller and outside off, shaping away, Sharma is happy to leave that.

OUT! LBW! What have you done Rohit Sharma? Southee traps him beautifully! Kept bowling outswingers, this one swung back in, Sharma raises his blade as he chooses not to play. The ball came back in sharply, however, and struck the back pad. He knew it straight away that this was out. Southee pleads for an LBW and the umpire does not hesitate to raise his finger. Sharma has a chat with Pujara to take the review but decides not to. A complete misjudgment from Rohit Sharma and he walks back into the hut. Tim Southee gets another.
Howout: lbw b Tim Southee

Commentary: Full ball around off, Kohli blocks it out.
Outside off, left alone.

That has gone over the stumps. Pujara did not expect that to come back in. It lands outside off and then jags back in. The is shorter. Pujara may have felt it would go away but to comes in. He leaves it and it goes over the stumps.
On middle, this is kept out nicely.
Good length again on of, blocked nicely.
On middle, blocked again.
A good short one to end! Left alone.
An outswinger, way outside off, Kohli shoulders arms.
Fuller on off, nipping away, Johli defends it towards covers.
Outside off, left alone.
FOUR LEG BYES! NASTY! Bowls a short ball on middle, Kohli looks to defend but is taken aback by the bounce. The ball hits right on the top of the helmet and goes over the slip cordon for a boundary.
Half-volley on middle and leg, Kohli flicks it through mid-wicket. Wagner goes after the ball and pushes back in time. He saves a run for his time. Three taken.
Length ball on off, blocked out.
WIDE! Short ball on middle, ducked under. Wided.
Full ball on off, flicked towards mid-wicket for a couple.
Another inswinger on off, worked towards mid on.
Length delivery on off, pushed back to the bowler.
Serves a length ball on off, nipping in, Kohli knocks it towards covers.
Good length delivery on off, Kohli looks to drive but the ball goes off the inside edge towards square leg. He picks up a couple.
Low full toss on middle, Kohli drives it towards mid on. India lead by 32 runs. THAT WILL BE STUMPS ON DAY 5.
Starts with a full ball, on middle, Kohli defends it out solidly.
A lenght ball, on off, Kohli defends it to the off side off the outer half.
A length ball, around middle and off, Kohli flicks it through mid-wicket for three. Lead by 35.
Back of a length ball, on leg, Pujara ducks under it.
A length ball, around middle, nips in. Pujara tucks it to the leg side.
Full, on leg, a little bit of inward movement. Pujara clips it through mid-wicket for a single. Moves to 13. Lead is 36.
Fuller length, on off, Pujara works it to mid on.
A length ball, on off, Puraja is solid in his defense.
Inswinger, full and on off, Pujara blocks it to the off side with an angled bat.
A length ball, on off, Pujara tucks it to short mid-wicket.
A touch fuller, on off, Pujara blocks it back to the bowler.
The big man starts his day with a maiden. Serves a length delivery, outside off. An easy leave for Cheteshwar Pujara.
Good length ball, outside off, moving away, Kohli shoulders his arms.
On a length, swinging away, Kohli just watches it go past him.
Another one away from the batsman. Outside off, nips away, Kohli lets it go to the keeper
Full and on off, Kohli pushes it through gully for a couple. Kohli wanted the third run, but Pujara was loud and clear with a 'NO'
Good length ball, outside off, Kohli leaves it alone.
Outside off, left alone by Kohli.
A length ball, on off, Pujara blocks it to cover.
Fires a full ball, on off, coming back in, Pujara is solid in his defense.
Fuller length delivery, around the pads, Pujara flicks it through fine leg for a single. Lead by 39.
A length ball, on off, kept out.

BEATEN! The first one to go past the edge today. On a length, outside off, Kohli anticipated it to come in, but the ball had other ideas as it swings away. Beats the outside edge as Kohli hangs his bat out looking to defend it.
JAFFA! A peach of a delivery by Kyle Jamieson yet again. A length delivery, outside off, nips away. Kohli yet again looks to defend it but misses. Jamieson has a smile on his face.
A length ball, around off, nipping away. Pujara lets it go to the keeper;
Good lenght ball, outside off, left alone.
A length ball, on off, Pujara pushes it to the off side.
A length ball, around middle and leg, Pujara defends it to mid on.
On a length, outside off, nipping away, Pujara leaves it alone.
Full, on off, nips in, Pujara defends it to cover off the front foot. A maiden for Tim Southee.
Good length ball, on off, nips in. Kohli comes forward and looks to defend it but misses and gets hit on the back pad. A loud appeal for LBW but the umpire is unmoved. Height was the issue.
A length ball, on off, kept out solidly.
A touch fuller, on off, Kohli blocks it out watchfully.
Good length delivery, outside off, Kohli leaves it alone.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Big, big wicket, as Kyle Jamieson gets the skipper for the second time in this Test. The big man gets the big fish. What an amazing start for the Kiwis, this will help boost their confidence. Good length ball, outside off, this one holds its line. Kohli was tempted by the width as he decided to push it through cover, but was unable to do so. The ball takes the outside edge and goes to the right of BJ Watling who takes a sitter. Can New Zealand use the momentum and capitalise on this wicket? This is the time they shift gears and go all out. Kohli could have left that one. Not sure why he played at that.
Howout: c BJ Watling b Kyle Jamieson

Commentary: A lenght ball, on off, Rahane defends it out.
Good length ball, outside off, left alone.
A full ball, on off, Cheteshwar Pujara is solid in his defense.
A length ball, on off, Pujara works it to the leg side.
A length ball, on the pads, Pujara clips it through square leg for a single.
Outside off, swinging away, left alone by Rahane.
An outswinger, full and on off, Rahane pushes it to cover.
Relentless stuff again! Length and on off, Pujara blocks it nicely.
Makes the batter play yet again by bowling it on the stumps, Pujara thoufh blocks it nicely.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! Outstanding from Jamieson. He got Kohli in his previous over and now Pujara. Game on, game well and truly on now. India are effectively 40 for 4. Once again, like Kohli, Pujara isn't sure whether to play at it or not. It is that kind of a line. Just outside off, the length too is perfect. Pujara hangs his bat out tentatively, it goes off the outside edge and it is taken nicely by Taylor at first slip. It is Kohli's wicket which opened the floodgates in the first innings, are we seeing something similar here?
Howout: c Ross Taylor b Kyle Jamieson

Commentary: Good length and on off, blocked.

A length ball, on off, Pant taps it to cover and gets a quick single. He is off the mark. The fielder has a shy at the bowler's end and Pant has to dive in. The replays show he was well inside the crease.
Solid! On off, kept out.

FOUR! Through the gap. On a length, outside off, Pant cuts it away through point uppishly but find the gap as the ball races towards the boundary. It seems he has to play his natural game and go for the kill.
On off, kept out.
Outside off, left alone by Pant.
A length ball, on off, coming back in, Pant defends it to point.
A full length delivery, outside off, Pant lets it go to the keeper.
Full and on off, Pant digs it out.
A lenght ball, on off, Rahane punches it through cover on his back foot. A couple.
An inswinger, on off, Rahane defends it out solidly.
A fullish length delivery, outside off, Rahane guides it to third man for another couple.
Back of a length ball, down the leg side. Rahane leaves it alone. BJ Watling does good to dive to his left and stop the ball.
LEG BYE! A full ball, on the pads, coming back in, Rahane looks to flick it but misses and gets gets hit on the pads. The ball rolls to the leg side. The batters sneak a single. Leg bye given.

DROPPED! Lucky, lucky Pant. A rarity in the slip cordon for New Zealand as Tim Southee drops a sitter. On a length, outside off, angling away, Pant looks to defend but misses and gets the outside edge as the ball flies to Tim Southee at second slip who does not hold the ball cleanly and Pant gets and extra life here. Kyle Jamieson deserved his third wicket of the day. He has been brilliant.
Back of a length and on off, Rahane defends it onto the ground.
Nicely played in the end! The outswinger, it is just outside off. Rahane watches it closely and leaves it alone.
Goes short now, Rahane does not back off, he pulls but is a touch early in the shot. It goes off the bottom half towards mid-wicket for one.
Not sure what Pant was doing there! He's probably a little nervous. He steps down the track and Southee bowls it fuller and outside off. Pant looks to drive but is beaten.

TWO MORE! Angled into the pads, this is worked through square leg for a couple. Runs scoring is important but what Pant did on the last ball was rash. He needs to be a little smart about now he goes about things.

Inside edge. He really seems to be jabbing at the balls with hard hands. Not good in such conditions. Again, he looks to defend this length ball outside off, ahead of his body. It jags back in. He gets an inside edge onto his pads.
On the off pole, kept out.
Another one on the stumps, Rahane keeps it out.
Now goes fuller, temting Rahane to drive. Ajinkya does so but plays it to covers.
Follows the full one with a short one on middle, Rahane spots it early and evades it.
On middle, defended nicely.
Really nicely bowled! An outswinger to end, fuller again. Rahane this time lets it go to the keeper.
Outside off, left alone.
Length again and outside off, Pant pushes at it, it goes off the outer half and the fielder at gully stops it.
Well played in the end! Southee brings it back in from outside off. Pant, probably due to the movement, looks to play it first but then realizes he does not need to and leaves it alone.
Another inswinger, this is fuller and outside off, left alone again.

FOUR! Shot! Superb use of the wrists there. This guy has strong forearms. Also, a less risky shot as he plays it with the movment. This one comes back in from outside off, Pant whips it through mid on and it races away.
Sensible! Outside off, left alone nicely.
Fuller and outside off, left alone.
A little too wide again, left alone again.
This time he attacks the stumps, kept out.
Another one on a length but the line is outside off, left alone.
Goes wide of the crease now and angles this one back in. A inswinger to follow after a few outswingers. Rahane plays it onto the ground.
On the fuller side, Rahane leans into it and strokes it to covers.
Good stop! Fuller and outside off, Pant hits it hard towards cover. The fielder dives to his left and makes a half stop. One taken.
Good length and on middle, this one comes back in a little. Rahane looks to block but it goes off the inner half through square leg for one.

FOUR! Pant goes after Wagner and gets the result he wanted. Skips down the track and this is bowled fuller and outside off. Pant actually makes this into a full ball, he smashes it past mid off for a boundary. Not a bad tactic from Pant but being attacking is different and being rash is different and he needs to be the former.
Clever! A boundary is followed by a good leave as this is bowled just outside off.
Wagner is fired up! On middle, this is defend back to the bowler. Who looks to pick it up but fails to do so. Does give him the stare.
Almost! Once again Pant is jabbing at the delivery which is just outside off, he plays it away from the body. He gets an inside edge onto the pads.
On off, Rahane guides it to point.

Not the right shot there! Especially against Boult who is getting it to tail back in a little. This is just outside off, just a little bit outside off. Extra bounce too. Rahane slashes at it. Too close to plays that shot. Luckily for India Rahane is beaten.
Nicely played! Gets on top of the bounce of this short one and pulls it all along the ground through square leg for one.
Sligjtly shorter in length and around off, Pant guides it to point.
Slips this one down the leg side. Pant looks to flick but misses.
Another run! For Pant this time! Angled into the pads, this is worked down to fine leg for one.
Solid! On off, defended.
Almost! This is angled into middle, Pant looks to work it on the leg side but he gets an inside edge onto the pads. It lobs up but lands well short of the bowler.
Solid! On middle, it is played back to the bowler.
On off, Pant plays it to mid on.
On middle, Pant shows the full face of the bat and keeps it out.
Slightly shorter in length. Pant hangs back and defends it onto the ground.
Fuller and on middle, Rahane works it towards the man at mid on.
Beaten again! This though was there to be hit. It is well wide outside off, Rahane goes after it but this one stays a touch low.
Two more! On middle, this is worked through square leg. Wagner in the deep runs to his left, slides and keeps it down to two. Good fielding.
On off, Rahane plays it to point.
That is a beauty! It lands on off and then moves away. Rahane is beaten as he tries to play the original line.

Really good stuff from Boult! Got the last one to angle away, this time he gets it back in after landing it on off, almsot the same position he bowled the last ball on. Rahane plays it late but it goes off the inner half on the leg side.
Fuller and on middle, Pant plays to back to the bowler.
Full and wide outside off, Pant opens the face of the bat but can't get it past gully.

EDGY FOUR! 100 up in a streaky manner! Pant comes down the track and Wagner bowls it fuller and outside off. This one shapes away a touch. Pant goes after it. It goes off the outside edge through the slip cordon and down to the third man fence.

This was rash! Pant comes down the track again. Wagner drags his length back a little. Pant does not get to the pitch of the ball but still swings. Gets beaten. Good from Rahane as he goes down to have a chat with Pant.
That is a good delivery. It is on a length and it lands on off, shapes away. Pant is half forward as he looks to block but is beaten.
Fuller this time and on middle, Pant works it to mid-wicket. This is a good contest between Pant and Wagner. End of a good over too from the pacers.
Good lenght ball, outside off, nipping away. Rahane comes forward looking to drive it through covers but misses as the ball bounces over the blade.
A length ball, on off, Rahane is solid in his defense.
On a length, down the leg side. Rahane pulls it to fine leg for a couple.
Full and on off, Rahane prods and drives it to cover. Where Latham dives to his right to make a spectacular one handed stop.
FOUR! SMOKED! A length ball, outside off. Rahane keeps his eyes on the ball, stays on the back foot and cuts it through point for a boundary.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! What a comeback by Trent Boult, as he finds the breakthrough as this partnership was looking dangerous. Rahane gave away his wicket, not a good way to depart, he will be gutted. On a length and down the leg side. Rahane tries to flick it but did not get a clean connection. The ball tickles off the gloves and BJ Watling moves to his left to take the catch. This is not looking good for India. Half the side back in the hut for them.
Howout: c BJ Watling b Trent Boult

Commentary: On middle, kept out.

NOT OUT! The Ball Tracker shows that the ball was missing stumps. A full length ball, around middle and leg, Pant looks to flick it but misses and gets rapped on the pads. Wagner and company make a loud appeal for LBW, the umpire is not interested and signals a leg bye as two is taken. We can see Ross Taylor from behind the stumps signaling to take the review, the Kiwis go for it. The Ultra Edge shows no bat involved. The Ball Tracker shows the ball was missing the stumps.
A full ball, on off, Pant clips it through mid-wicket for a couple.
A touch short, on off, Pant pulls it through mid-wicket for a single.
Good length ball, on off, Jadeja looks to pull it but does not middle it.
A length ball, on off, Jadeja pushes it through cover for a couple.
A touch fuller, on off, Pant guides it to point and gets a single.
A length ball, on off, Jadeja keeps it out.
A length ball, on off, Jadeja is solid in his defense.
FOUR! Nicely played. A length ball, on the pads, Jadeja clips it through mid-wicket as the ball races towards the boundary.
A length ball, on off, Jadeja works it to mid on.
Back of a length ball, on off, nipping away, Jadeja sways away from the line of the delivery.
A length ball, on the pads, Pant flicks and gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Full, on the pads, Pant removes his front leg and flicks it through square leg for a single.

FOUR! Beautifully player. Jadeja is also having a go here. Two boundaries in two overs for him. A length ball, around middle and leg, Jadeja clips it through mid-wicket. Two fielders give it a chase, but the ball wins the race and finds the boundary.

A length ball, on off, Jadeja works it to mid off, and takes off looking for a run. He is half way down the track, before Pant shouts NOO and sends him back. Meanwhile, the fielder lifts the ball and throws it to the striker's end. Jadeja is racing back to the crease and reaches comfortably in the end. But the throw is a little wide, as Watling does not collect it well, and might have hurt himself in the process.

This time a direct hit, is Ravindra Jadeja in trouble here? A length ball on off Jadeja pushes it to cover for a single. the fielder has a shy at the stumps and hits it strightaway. The umpire decides to take it upstairs. The replays show the batsman is inside the crease.
On off, kept out.
On a length, around off, Jadeja defends it solidly.
A touch fuller, on off, Jadeja pushes it to cover for a single.
A length ball, on off, Pant flicks it to mid-wicket for another single.
A length ball, around off, Jadeja stays back and defends it out.
A touch fuller, outside off, Jadeja prods and blocks it onto the pitch.
Good length ball, outside off, nipping away, Jadeja lets it go to the keeper.
A fullish delivery, on the pads, Pant flicks it to mid-wicket for a single.
A touch short, down the leg side. Jadeja leaves it alone.
A length ball, around middle and leg, Jadeja blocks it back to the bowler.
Back of a length ball, on the bodyline, Jadeja ducks under it.
Angles in a length ball, on middle, Jadeja tucks it to the man at short leg.
OUCH! A short ball, around middle, coming back in, Jadeja takes this one on the body. THAT WILL BE LUNCH ON DAY 6. INDIA LEADS BY 98.
Starts off on a length and outside off, Pant leaves it alone. Good delivery to begin. Kind of similar to the line Pant edged but the left-hander left it this time.
Well, that leave was a sighted. Straightaway comes down the track on the second ball. Jamieson lands it on a length around off. Pant swings but misses.
Hits the length hard and lands it on off, extra bounce for Kyle. Pant takes a hand off the handle and plays it onto the ground.
First run of the session! On off, Pant drops it towards cover and gets to the other end.
Length again and angling away. Left alone.
Just outside off, Jadeja plays it well by dropping his hands. Just a single from the over then.
Short and down the leg side. Pant looks to pull but misses.
Another short one. This one has more bounce but it is yet again down the leg side. Pant looks to pull again but misses.
The lead is now a 100! On the pads, this is worked down to fine leg for one.
One more short one down the leg side. This is left alone.
On the shorter side and on middle, Jadeja defends it.
One more short one to end. Evaded.
On off, it is defended.
Length and this one takes off after landing. Pant looks to defend but then pulls his bat out of the way.
On off, kept out.
Another one on the stumps, blocked again.
Two more! Length and on off, this is pushed through covers for two.
On off, kept out.
Back of a length ball, on the body line, Jadeja looks to pull it away, but does not middle it as the ball rolls to square leg for a single.
BYE! A length ball, on off, Pant goes for the scoop shot but misses. As the ball goes over BJ Watling. The batters sneak a run. Bye given.
On a length, on off, Jadeja is solid in his defense.
A touch short, around off, Jadeja hops and defends it watchfully.
Good length ball, on the pads, Jadeja tucks it to the leg side.
LEG BYE! A short ball, on off, nips in, Jadeja looks to defend but misses, as the ball hits on his arm and rolls towards the short third man region. The batters sneak a single. leg bye given.
A nice short one outside off, Jadeja lets it go to the keeper.
Outside off again, need not play at those.
One more delivery outside off, Jadeja lets it through.
Nicely played in the end! Good length and just outside off. Jadeja drops his hands and lets it be.

That is a beauty! Had it been a touch fuller. Jadeja was a goner. This starts on off, the length is slightly shorter. This one shapes in late. Jadeja fails to get his bat down in time, luckily for him, it goes over the stump.
Outside off, left alone.
Audacious from Pant! He is early in position to play the reverse sweep. Wagner still bangs it short. He plays it down towards third man for one.
Shortish again, this one does not bounce a lot. Jadeja looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
One more short one but down the leg side. Evaded. The short balls aren't causing a lot of trouble.
Outside off, left alone.
Another short one, it is evaded.
One more short ball, ducked under.
Dishes a full length ball, outside off, Pant tries to chase it but misses.
Back of a length ball, on off, Pant looks to pull this one away but only manages to get an inside edge onto the pitch.
Good length ball, on off, Pant taps it towards mid off and takes off. Conway runs towards the ball and kicks it on the stumps, as Pant dives to reach in safely. That was some kick by Conway.
Good length ball, coming across the left hander. Jadeja leaves it for the keeper.
A length ball, around off, moving away, Jadeja leaves it alone. But the ball dies on it's way to the keeper.
On a length, outside off, Jadeja pushes it through the cover region, as the batters take three.
On a length, on off, Jadeja defends it back to the bowler.
Back of a length ball, on leg, the ball takes off after hitting the deck, Jadeja ducks under it.

Ahh.. that was close. Serves a touch short delivery, around the hips, Jadeja hops and defends it to the leg side, as the ball goes over the man at short leg. If he could've stayed up Jadeja was a goner.
A bouncer now on middle, Jadeja ducks under it.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Neil Wagner's patience finally pays off. He gets his first wicket of the day. This is an important breakthrough as both the batters were looking very well settled. Wagner goes short for a long long time. And this one time he changes his length, and a solid innings of Ravindra Jadeja comes to an end. Serves a good length ball, across the batsman, swinging away, outside off, Jadeja looks to defend but gets an outside edge and BJ Watling, with his dislocated finger takes an easy catch behind the stumps.
Howout: c BJ Watling b Neil Wagner

Commentary: A full length ball, on off, Ashwin defends it out.
On off, blocked.
A fullish delivery, on middle and leg, Pant blocks it to mid on.
A short ball, on off, Pant pulls it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
A length ball, on off, Ashwin defends it to the off side,
BEATEN! A full length delivery, around off, it nips away, Ashwin looks to push it but misses as the ball moves away from his blade.
A bouncer on off, Ashwin leaves it for the keeper.
A short ball, on the body line, Pant pulls it to square leg for a single.
A touch short, on off, Ashwin tries to take it, as he pulls it to mid-wicket but cannot find the gap.
Another short ball, on off, Ashwin pulls it to mid-wicket uppishly this time, as it land just in front of Jamieson at mid-wicket.
Good length ball, on off, Ashwin pulls it through the square leg region this time for a couple.

A length ball, on off, Ashwin goes back and pulls it over mid-wicket, Williamson leaps but the ball flies over him to the deep. The batters take a single. Had Jamieson still been positioned at mid-wicket, Ashwin had to walk back to the shed.
Full, around middle, Pant drives it back to the bowler.
BEATEN! A good length ball, outside off, Ashwin looks to poke it out but misses as the ball beats the outside edge.
A touch fuller, on off, Ashwin defends it to cover.
A length ball, on off, Ashwin tucks it to mid-wicket.
A full length delivery, outside off, Aswhin looks to heave it away but misses as the ball bounces over the blade.
Good length ball, outside off, Ashwin pushes it to cover.
A maiden for Kyle Jamieson! A good length ball, outside off, holding the line. An easy leave for Ashwin.
A length ball, around middle, Pant pulls it to square leg for a single.
A length ball, on off, Ashwin steered it down past gully. The batters come back for three comfortably.
A length ball, on the body, Pant works it towards fine leg for a single. Moves to 38.
A length ball, around the hips, Ashwin pulls it through square leg for another single. Moves to 7.
Good length ball, down the leg side. Pant looks to pull this away but misses.
A single to end the over! A length ball, on off, Pant pulls it through mid-wicket for a single.
Serves a length ball, on off, Pant defends it watchfully.
Good length ball, outside off, moving away, an easy leave for Pant.
A full length ball, on off, Pant defends it to cover off his front foot.
Fullish, around middle, Pant blocks it back to the bowler.
A touch short, on off, Pant pulls it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Serves a length ball, on off, Ashwin keeps it out.
Good length and on middle, blocked.
Outside off, left alone.
Another one outside off, not played at.
Southee once again starts this from outside off, he looks to bring it back in. Does not swing. Left alone.
Another leave as this is yet again bowled outside off.
Really nice shot but just for one. Fuller and outside off, this is driven through covers for one. Pant retains strike.
Outside off,eft alone.

OUT! TAKEN! Pant is out of here! The last recognized batter has to walk back and this is exactly what India wouldn't have wanted. A lot of people would also question the shot but that is how Pant plays. You live by the sword and you also die by it. That though is some catch by Nicholls, absolutely stunning. Pant comes down the track and Boult bowls it on middle. He gets some extra bounce. Pant swings but this goes off the top edge over point. Nicholls runs back and takes it outstandingly. Never easy when you have run back like this and it is over your shoulder. New Zealand into the bowlers now. The lead is just 124. Still over 55 overs left in the day.
Howout: c Henry Nicholls b Trent Boult

Commentary: Fuller and on off, Ashwin looks to drive but it goes off the inner half on the leg side.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! Ashwin is now a goner! It is now falling apart all too quickly for the Indians. Another poor shot. Boult has two and what a change by Williamson. He brings him on and he strikes gold. This is full and outside off, inviting Ashwin for the drive. He goes for it but away from the body. It goes off the outside edge and it is taken by Ross Taylor at first slip.
Howout: c Ross Taylor b Trent Boult

Commentary: Catch is the cry but it lands in no mans land! Shorter and on middle, Sharma looks to defend but it hits the splice and lobs on the off side.
Outside off, left alone.
Slips this one down the leg side, Shami looks to flick but misses.
Good length and on off, blocked.
FOUR! Cut away! Any kind of runs now are important. This is short and wide outside off, Shami slashes it through point for a boundary.
Fuller and on off, blocked.
FOUR! Pulled hard and another boundary. Lead over 130 now. Short and on middle, Shami pulls it hard, it is in the gap in the square leg region and it races a away to the fence.
Solid now! On middle, this is defended nicely.
On middle, this is worked down to fine leg for one.
Goes for the yorker, it is on middle, jammed out.
Back of a length and on off, this is guided through point for one.
Audacious from Ishant. He goes after one really wide and outside off. Misses by a long way.
Shorter and on the body, this is nudged on the leg side.
Fuller and on middle, Sharma drives it towards mid off.
EDGY FOUR! Handy, handy runs all of these. This is full and outside off, Shami swings, it goes off the outside edge over the slip cordon for a boundary.

OUT! TAKEN! Outstanding from New Zealand. Everything they have done today has gone to plan. They had got in a fly slip on this ball and that is where the catch is taken. One shot too many by Shami.
