This is full and on middle, Shami swings but it goes off the outside edge and it is a simple catch for  Latham.
Howout: c Tom Latham b Tim Southee

Commentary: A length ball, on off, Bumrah defends it solidly.
Good length ball, outside off, Bumrah lets it go to the keeper.
A fullish delivery, on off, Bumrah defends it to cover.

OUT! CAUGHT AT SLIPS! There goes last man, Southee strikes on his last ball. Bumrah does not disturb the score at all, as he departs on a duck. A length ball, on middle, Bumrah looks to defend but gets an outside edge as the ball flies to Tom Latham at second slip who does not miss such sitters. NEW ZEALAND NEED 139 MORE RUNS TO WIN.
Howout: c Tom Latham b Tim Southee

Commentary: Starts with a length ball, on off, Latham look to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
A length ball, on off, coming in, Latham defends it to cover.
Back of a length delivery, outside off, Latham lets it go to the keeper.
Serves a full length ball, on off, Latham drives it to cover.
Angles in a length ball, on off, Latham defends it back to the bowler.
On off, Latham is solid in his defense.
Back of a length ball, on off, Conway looks to hook it away but cannot find the gap.
First run on the board for New Zealand! A length ball, on the pads, Conway flicks it to square leg and gets a single.
Good length ball, outside off, the ball takes off after landing. Latham leaves it alone.
Angles in a length ball, outside off, Latham shoulders his arms, but the ball comes back in a long way as the ball passes over the stumps.
Another one shaping in, a good length ball, outside off, Latham shoulders arms to it.
A touch fuller, on off, Latham defends it to cover. Just a single off the over. A tudy over by Mohammed Shami.
Good length ball, outside off, swinging away, Conway leaves it alone.
On a length, outside off, holding the line, Conway lets it go to the keeper.
Full and on off, Conway defends it to cover.
On off, kept out.
Good length ball, outside off, moving away. An easy leave for Devon Conway.
Angles in a length ball, on off, Conway defends it watchfully.
A length ball, on off, Latham is solid in his defense.
A length ball, on off, Latham stays back and defends it back to the bowler.
A touch short, outside off, Latham is baited with the height as he looks to pull this away but misses as the ball bounces over the blade.
Angles in a length ball, on off, Latham defends it out.
Good length ball, outside off, Latham leaves it alone.
FOUR LEG BYES! A full ball, on the pads, Latham looks to flick but misses, as the balls clips the pads and rolls toward the fine leg fence for a boundary. Leg bye given.
A length ball, on the pads, Conway looks to flick it but misses as the ball clips the pads and rolls towards square leg. Single taken. Leg bye.
Outside off, left alone.
Angled in a length ball, around middle, Latham defends and gets an inside edge onto the pads.
On a length, around off, Latham pushes it through point for a couple.
Full length delivery, on the pads, Latham flicks it to the on side for a couple again. Good running.
A length ball, on off Latham defends it to cover.
Outside off, left alone.
A touch short, on off, Conway pull it straight to mid on.
A length ball, on off, Conway is solid in his defense.
BEATEN! Nicely bowled by Shami! This is fullish and outside off, Conway looks to defend but misses. The ball beats the outside edge.
That is some carry! A good length ball, outside off, the ball takes off after hitting the deck. Conway shoulders his arms.
FOUR! Nice shot by Conway! A full length delivery, on off, Conway plays the on drive as the ball races towards the boundary at long on.
On off, Latham pushes it to covers.
A short one on the body, this is pulled down to fine leg for one.
Outside off, left alone.
Another one outside off, left alone. This has been the problem for Bumrah. He has been way too wide outside off and not made the batter play often.
FOUR! Nice and fine! He needed to be straighter but this is way too straight, it is worked fine on the leg side and it races away to the fence.
Beaten! Length and on off, this one angles away. Conway looks to defend but is beaten. Better from Bumrah. He needs to hit these lines a lot more often.
Beaten! Length and outside off, this one holds its line. Latham is beaten as he tries to block.
Full again and outside off. Left alone.
Back of a length and on middle, blocked.
Almsot! Length and outside off, Latham pushes at it but is beaten.
Back of a length and on off, this is pushed to cover.
A beauty to end! This is angled in from around the wicket. It lands around off and then moves away. Latham is beaten as he tries to block. THAT WILL BE TEA ON DAY 6!
Starts with a length ball, on off, Conway defends it to cover off the front foot.
Good length ball, outside off, moving away, an easy leave for Devon Conway.
Full and outside off, nips away, Conway lets it go to the keeper.
A length ball, on middle, Conway looks to pull it but it hits the pad and lobs on the off side.
On off, kept out.
A maiden for Bumrah. Good length ball, outside off, Conway shoulders his arms.
Flatter around off, Latham stays back and punches it through cover and gets a single.
Loopy ball, full and on middle, Conway defends it solidly.
Tossed up, on off, Conway defends it to the on side off the outer half.
Loopy ball, around middle, Conway tucks it to the leg side for a single.
Flatter and short, on off, Latham goes back and pushes it to cover.

Almost! A loopy ball around middle, Latham dances down the track and looks to flick it but the ball takes the leading  edge and flies over the bowler's head. Ashwin leaps but was not enough to get hold of the ball.
LEG BYE! Full ball on the pads, Conway looks to flick but misses and the ball rolls to the fine leg region off the pads. Single taken. Leg bye.
Outside off, left alone.
BEATEN! A length ball, outside off, swinging away, Latham looks to defend but  misses.
Another peach of a delivery! Good length ball, outside off, swinging away, Latham was looking to defend it out but misses as the ball zips past the outside edge.
Play and a miss! On a length, outside off, Latham misses his defense as the ball beats the outside edge.
A length ball, on off, Latham defends it back to the bowler.
Loopy ball, on off, Conway defends it solidly.
On off, kept out.
Floated and on off, Conway is solid in his defense.
Loopy ball, on off, Conway pushes it to cover.
Floated on off, Conway uses his feet and defends it to cover.
On off, kept out by Conway.
A length ball, outside off, Latham pushes it through cover for three.
FOUR LEG BYE! Good length ball, on the pads, Conway looks to flick but misses. While the ball clips the pads and rolls past diving Rishabh Pant for a boundary at fine leg.
Angles across, a length ball, on off, swinging away, Conway makes a smart leave.
BEATEN! On a length, outside off, this one is quicker. Conway looks to play at it but misses.
FOUR! Top-notch by Devon Conway. Nicely played. A length ball, on off, Conway punches it through cover for a boundary. More 106 needed to win.
Outside off, left alone.
Loopy ball, on off, Latham goes back and works it to mid on.
Tossed up, on off, Latham defends it solidly off the front foot.

OUT! STUMPED! It is Ravichandran Ashwin who draws the first blood. Prior to this ball, Pant was advising Ashwin to toss it up and well that certainly worked. Toosed up, around off, Latham comes down the track and swings his blade wildly. But completely misses it. The ball goes through him, Pant collects the ball and disturbs the stumps. The fans are cheering to their core. Maybe just maybe there is some hope building now.
Howout: st Rishabh Pant b Ravichandran Ashwin

Commentary: Loopy ball, on off, Williamson nudges it to the leg side.
Flatter and on off, Williamson stays back and pushes it to cover.
Floated and on off, WIlliamson is solid in his defense.

A length ball, down the leg side, Conway looks to flick but misses. Rishabh Pant dives to his left to make a great stop. Wait, he also says he heard some noise, but it was not enough to convince his team-mates.
A length ball, on off, Conway pushes it to point and gets a single. Ravindra Jadeja picks the ball and hits the stumps at the strikers end. But Williamson was well inside the crease.
A length ball, on off, Williamson pushes it to cover for a single.
FOUR! PULLED AWAY! Back of a length ball, on off, Conway pulls it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Good length ball, on off, Conway looks to defend it and does so but only with his gloves. This must've hurt him.
A length ball, on off, Conway drives it to cover.
Loopy ball, around middle, Williamson defends it to the leg side.
Floated on off, Williamson prods and defends it watchfully.
Loopy ball, around middle, Williamson goes back and defends it out.
Flighted on off, kept out.

NOT OUT! The Ball Tracker saves Kane Williamson, as the replays show the ball was missing the stumps. A loopy ball, around middle and leg, Williamson prods and looks to sweep it but misses. The ball goes through to come in contact with the pads and rolls towards the fine leg region. A loud appeal for LBW and the umpire raises his finger in a flash. Kane Williamson is surprised with the decision and takes the review straightaway. The Ultra Edge shows no bat involved. The Ball Tracker shows the wickets are missing. The crowd went silent as soon as this was played on the big screen, whereas it was a big, big relief for the New Zealand supporters.
Flatter and on off, Williamson punches it through covers for three.
Another appeal but turned down. On middle, this pitches and then straightens. Williamson looks to play it with the angle but misses. He gets hit near the box.
Angled on middle, Williamson works it through square leg for a couple.
Well bowled! Looks to get it back in from outside off. Does not bring it in enough to make the batter play.
Good length and on off, Williamson blocks it out.
Back of a length and on off, Williamson pushes it to covers.
Another one on a length and around off, Kane strokes it to mid off.
Loopy ball, on off, Conway works it to mid on.

OUT! LBW! Ravichandran Ashwin strikes for the second time post the Tea break. This is turing out to be a cracker of an event. This is the huge wicket of Conway, Ashwin bowls a floated delivery around off, which turns in. Conway looks to defend it but misses and gets rapped on the pads. A loud appeal from Ashwin and company. The umpire raises his finger in a flash. Conway is disappointed as he walks to the other end to have a word with the skipper. They decide not to take it upstairs which is a wise decision. India aren't going down without a fight. They are still in it.
Howout: lbw b Ravichandran Ashwin

Commentary: Floated on off, taylor defends it solidly.
Tossed up, on off, Taylor flicks it to the leg side.
Loopy ball, on off, Taylor defends it onto the pitch.
A wicket maiden for Ravichandran Ashwin. Floated on off, Taylor is solid in his defense.

A length ball, on off, coming back in, Williamson looks to flick it but misses and gets hit on the pads. The crowd is appealing here. But this one is just too high, the umpire nods his head and denies.
Length ball, down the leg side , Williamson looks to flick it but misses.
A length ball, around the hips, Williamson hops and tucks it to square leg for a couple.
Good length ball, outside off, Williamson leaves it for the keeper.
Quicker, on a length, outside off, Williamson shoulders his arms.
Angles in a full ball, on off, Williamson defends it to cover.
Tossed up on off, blocked.
Another one floated up on off, kept out.
Flatter and on off, Taylor defends it.
Floats it up yet again on off, defended.
On off, Taylor pushes it back to the bowler.
Another maiden! On middle, Taylor plays it back to the bowler.
Back of a length and on off, Williamson pushes it to covers.
Outside off, left alone again.
A yes and no situation there! On middle, this is worked to mid-wicket. Williamson initially calls for a run but then sends his partner back.
Outside off, left alone.
One more ball outside off, Williamson leaves it alone.
On middle, blocked.
Loopy ball, around middle, Taylor tucks it to short mid-wicket.
Tossed up, on off, the ball curles away a bit, Taylor defends it watchfully.
Floated on off, Taylor ficks it to mid on.
Tossed up, on off, kept out.
Flighted on off, Taylor pushes it to mid on.
On off, Taylor works it to mid on.
A length ball, on the pads, Williamson flicks it to square leg and gets a single. Oh the umpire signals a leg bye, this one is off the pads.

On a length, outside off, Taylor, punches it straight to point, on a bounce. Ravindra Jadeja collects the ball and throws it up in the air, as he gets everybody in the crown on their feet. But he is just having fun.
On off, kept out.
FOUR! This one find the gap. Well played by Taylor. A lenght ball, outside off, Taylor guides it through point for a boundary.
A length ball, on off, Taylor flicks it to square leg for a single.
A length ball, on off, Williamson defends it watchfully.
On middle, this is worked to mid-wicket.
FOUR! Hammered! This is tossed up on off, Taylor whips it powerfully over mid-wicket for a boundary.
That has spun big! This lands outside off and then spins back in. Sharply. Taylor look ka to defend but leaves a gap between bat and pad. It sneaks through and goes over the stumps.
FOUR! A little too full and it is put away. Runs starting to come now. It is outside off, Taylor drives it through covers.
On middle, blocked.
Loopy ball on middle, kept out.
Outside off, left alone.
On off, blocked.
On off, this is guided to point.
On the stumps, blocked.
FOUR! Put away! India leaking boundaries now and all the pressure that was built has been released. Shorter and on off, this is slapped through covers for a boundary.
On middle, kept out.
Floats it up on off, kept out.
On middle, this is pushed to mid on.
Floats it up on off, kept out.
On middle, this is eased down to long on for one.
Flatter and on off, kept out.
On middle, this is pushed to mid on.
Shorter and outside off, Taylor slashes at it but ends up chopping it on the off side.
FOUR! Hammered away! This is short and begging to be hit. Taylor smashes it through covers for another boundary. Only 70 needed now.
Good length and on off, kept out.
Fuller and on middle, this is driven but to mid on.
Another single! This is outside off, it is guided down to third man for one.
Outside off, left alone.
On middle, this is worked towards mid-wicket for one.
Another single as this is clipped on the leg side. Jadeja has overstepped.
On middle, kept out.
Another one on off, kept out.
Beaten! This is flatter and outside off, Taylor looks to drive but the ball spins away. He is beaten. He does well to not lift the back foot.
A single again! On middle, it is nudged around the corner for one.
On middle, blocked.
On off, kept out.
One more flighted delivery on off, kept out.
Flatter and on off, this is worked to mid-wicket.
Takes one! On off, it is worked towards mid-wicket.
On off, Williamson pushes it through covers for one.
Loopy ball on off, defended.
Full on middle, it is worked to mid-wicket.
Three more! Shorter and outside off, it is cut through point. The fielder at cover-point hares after it, dives and saves a run for his side.
On off, this is pushed to covers.
Quicker and on off, defended.
FOUR! Finds the fence this time but it is off the bat of Williamson. Short and outside off again. This is cut through point for a boundary.
A good delivery to end but the damage was done earlier in the over. This lands on off and then turns away. Williamson prods forward to defend but is beaten.
On middle, defended.
Outside off, left alone.
Fuller and on off, Taylor drives it to covers.

EDGED BUT DROPPED! Pujara the culprit. Bumrah would have loved a wicket. Maybe it would not have made a difference to the result but surely t his confidence. A good delivery, length and around off, this one holds its line. Taylor looks to defend but it goes off the outside edge towards first slip. Pujara probably was a little late to move to his left and hence, spills it. He might have felt the keeper was going for it.
A single now! On middle, this is worked on the leg side for one.
On middle, kept out.
A huge appeal but turned down! Maybe the impact was outside off. This is bowled outside off. Taylor looks to sweep but misses. It hits the pad. A huge appeal but turned down.
On middle, kept out.
On off, this is pushed to cover.
On middle again, this is nudged to mid-wicket.
On middle, kept out.
Another one on the stumps, blocked.
FOUR! SMOKED! A length ball, on off, Williamson gets to the pitch of the delivery and creams it through covers for a boundary. 50 more to win.
A length ball, on off, Williamson pushes it to cover.
On off, kept out.
A length ball, on off, Williamson guides it to point.
BEATEN! Serves a length ball, outside off, Williamson looks to defend it but misses as the ball beats the outside edge. This was very close.
A yorker, on the money by Bumrah. Williamson defends it back to the bowler.
Loopy ball, on off, Taylor prods and keeps it out.
Around leg, Taylor tucks it to the leg side.
Floated around middle, Taylor defends it solidly.
On off, kept out.
Floated around middle, Taylor defends it on his front foot.
Full, on the pads, Taylor flicks it to square leg and gets a single.
A length ball, on off, Taylor flicks it to the leg side for a couple.
A full length ball, on off, Taylor defends it solidly.
On off, kept out.

OUCH! This must've hurt! Back of a length ball, coming in from outside off, Taylor looks to defend but completely misjudges it. The ball bounces off the track and hits Taylor on his helmet. There was almost an inch of gap between Taylor's defense and the helmet.
Outside off, left alone.
Angled into the pads, Bumrah looks to flick but misses to get hit high on the pads.
On middle, kept out.
Bog turn! This lands outside off, on a driving length. Williamson looks to drive but the ball turns away and goes past the outside edge.
On middle, kept out.
FOUR! Nice and fine! On the pads, Williamson plays the paddle sweep, he plays it fine and it races away to the fence.
On the stumps again, it is defended nicely.
Fuller and on off, it is driven to covers.
Another one that has jumped at Taylor. A  length ball, on off, the ball gets an extra bounce off the pitch. This time he manages to defend it with his blade.
A length ball, on off, Taylor keeps it out.
Full and on off, Taylor drives it to cover.
FOUR! Fine enough for four more. A short ball, on the pads, Taylor uses Bumrah's pace and clips it fine for a boundary. This also brings up the 100 for New Zealand.
Play and a miss! On a length, outside off, Taylor looks to defend it but misses.
Angles in a full ball, on off, Taylor pushes it to cover. 39 more to win.
On off, kept out.
Tossed up on off, Williamson defends it out.
Flatter, on off, Williamson goes back and cuts it towards point for a single.
Floated on off, Taylor flicks it to mid-wicket.
